<TITLE> Judgment in RU arson case shifted to Dec 12 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Rajshahi, Dec 6 (bdnews24.com) A Rajshahi court Thursday postponed the verdict in the DGFI car torching case, filed during the August student demonstrations at Rajshahi University, to Dec 12. Rajshahi additional chief judicial magistrate Ruhul Amin set the new date saying that his verdict report is not yet complete. The accused in the caseRU geology and mining professors Chowdhury Sarwar Jahan Shajal and Golam Sabbir Sattar Tapu, deputy chief information officer Sadequl Islam and former VC Prof Faisul Islam Faruqui's driver Ataur Rahman Atawere produced in the court. The 10 other accused in the case are students who have so far evaded arrest. Charges were framed on Sept 18 and a total of 24 witnesses gave depositions in the case beginning Sept 24. The court set the verdict date on Nov 27, after cross-examinations and arguments were concluded. In the wake of the Dhaka University student demonstrations in August, Rajshahi University also witnessed large scale student-police clashes on its campus on August 22, during which a rickshaw-puller was shot dead. Rajshahi Directorate General of Forces Intelligence (DGFI) assistant director Shawkat Ali filed a case on Aug 23, with Motihar Police Station, over the torching of a DGFI car. Motihar police submitted a charge sheet accusing the two RU teachers, two officials and 10 students on Sept 1. Professors Sarwar Jahan and Sabbir Sattar, and driver Ataur Rahman, were sent to jail by the court after surrender on Sept 11. A verdict was delivered Tuesday in a separate case filed against six RU teachers for instigating students to stage the August demonstrations. Four teachers were found guilty and sentenced to two years' imprisonment and two were acquitted. bdnews24.com/c
